columns.name: organisation_key
columns.dc:title: Provider Organisation Key
columns.schema:description: A sequence of characters which uniquely identifies the provider organisation. Assigned by the Primary Health Network.

columns.name: organisation_name
columns.dc:title: Provider Organisation - Name
columns.schema:description: The name of the provider organisation.

columns.name: organisation_type
columns.dc:title: Provider Organisation - Type
columns.schema:description: The type of the provider organisation.

columns.name: organisation_state
columns.dc:title: Provider Organisation - State
columns.schema:description: The state that the provider organisation operates in.

columns.name: organisation_path
columns.dc:title: Organisation Path
columns.schema:description: A sequence of colon separated Organisation Codes that fully specifies the upload organisation.

columns.name: practitioner_key
columns.dc:title: Practitioner Key
columns.schema:description: A sequence of characters which uniquely identifies a practitioner.

columns.name: practitioner_category
columns.dc:title: Practitioner - Category
columns.schema:description: The type or category of the practitioner, as represented by a code.

columns.name: cultural_training_flag
columns.dc:title: Practitioner - Cultural Training Flag
columns.schema:description: A flag to represent whether a practitioner has completed a recognised training programme in the delivery of culturally safe mental health services to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, as represented by a code.

columns.name: practitioner_year_of_birth
columns.dc:title: Practitioner - Year of Birth
columns.schema:description: The year the practitioner was born.

columns.name: gender
columns.dc:title: Practitioner - Gender
columns.schema:description: The term ‘gender’ refers to the way in which a person identifies their masculine or feminine characteristics. A persons gender relates to their deeply held internal and individual sense of gender and is not always exclusively male or female. It may or may not correspond to their sex assigned at birth.

columns.name: atsi_status
columns.dc:title: Practitioner - Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Status
columns.schema:description: Whether a person identifies as being of Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander origin, as represented by a code.

columns.name: practitioner_active
columns.dc:title: Practitioner - Active
columns.schema:description: A flag to represent whether a practitioner is actively delivering services. This is a system field that is aimed at helping organisations manage practitioner codes.

columns.name: organisation_path
columns.dc:title: Organisation Path
columns.schema:description: A sequence of colon separated Organisation Codes that fully specifies the upload organisation.

columns.name: client_key
columns.dc:title: Client Key
columns.schema:description: This is a number or code assigned to each individual referred to the commissioned organisation. The client identifier is unique and stable for each individual at the level of the PMHC top level organisation.

columns.name: slk
columns.dc:title: Client - Statistical Linkage Key
columns.schema:description: A key that enables two or more records belonging to the same individual to be brought together.

columns.name: date_of_birth
columns.dc:title: Client - Date of Birth
columns.schema:description: The date on which an individual was born.

columns.name: est_date_of_birth
columns.dc:title: Client - Estimated Date of Birth Flag
columns.schema:description: The date of birth estimate flag records whether or not the client’s date of birth has been estimated.

columns.name: gender
columns.dc:title: Client - Gender
columns.schema:description: The term ‘gender’ refers to the way in which a person identifies their masculine or feminine characteristics. A persons gender relates to their deeply held internal and individual sense of gender and is not always exclusively male or female. It may or may not correspond to their sex assigned at birth.

columns.name: atsi_status
titles: Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Status
columns.dc:title: Client - Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Status
columns.schema:description: Whether a person identifies as being of Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander origin, as represented by a code.

columns.name: country_of_birth
columns.dc:title: Client - Country of Birth
columns.schema:description: The country in which the client was born, as represented by a code.

columns.name: main_lang_at_home
columns.dc:title: Client - Main Language Spoken at Home
columns.schema:description: The language reported by a client as the main language other than English spoken by that client in his/her home (or most recent private residential setting occupied by the client) to communicate with other residents of the home or setting and regular visitors, as represented by a code.

columns.name: prof_english
columns.dc:title: Client - Proficiency in Spoken English
columns.schema:description: The self-assessed level of ability to speak English, asked of people whose first language is a language other than English or who speak a language other than English at home.

columns.name: organisation_path
columns.dc:title: Organisation Path
columns.schema:description: A sequence of colon separated Organisation Codes that fully specifies the upload organisation.

columns.name: episode_key
columns.dc:title: Episode Key
columns.schema:description: This is a number or code assigned to each episode. The Episode Key is unique and stable for each episode at the level of the organisation.

columns.name: episode_start_date
columns.dc:title: Episode - Start Date
columns.schema:description: The date on which the client formally or statistically commences an episode of mental health care.

columns.name: episode_end_date
columns.dc:title: Episode - End Date
columns.schema:description: The date on which an episode of mental health care is formally or statistically ended.

columns.name: referral_date
columns.dc:title: Episode - Referral Date
columns.schema:description: The date the referrer made the referral.

columns.name: princ_focus_of_treatment
columns.dc:title: Episode - Principal Focus of Treatment Plan
columns.schema:description: The range of activities that best describes the overall services intended to be delivered to the client throughout the course of the episode. For most clients, this will equate to the activities that account for most time spent by the service provider.

columns.name: client_postcode
columns.dc:title: Episode - Area of usual residence, postcode
columns.schema:description: The Australian postcode of the client.

columns.name: labour_force_status
columns.dc:title: Episode - Labour Force Status
columns.schema:description: The self-reported status the person currently has in being either in the labour force (employed/unemployed) or not in the labour force, as represented by a code.

columns.name: employment_participation
columns.dc:title: Episode - Employment Participation
columns.schema:description: Whether a person in paid employment is employed full-time or part-time, as represented by a code.

columns.name: income_source
columns.dc:title: Episode - Source of Cash Income
columns.schema:description: The source from which a person derives the greatest proportion of his/her income, as represented by a code.

columns.name: ndis_participant
columns.dc:title: Episode - NDIS Participant
columns.schema:description: Is the client a participant in the National Disability Insurance Scheme?, as represented by a code.

columns.name: marital_status
columns.dc:title: Episode - Marital Status
columns.schema:description: A person’s current relationship status in terms of a couple relationship or, for those not in a couple relationship, the existence of a current or previous registered marriage, as represented by a code.

columns.name: suicide_referral_flag
columns.dc:title: Episode - Suicide Referral Flag
columns.schema:description: Identifies those individuals where a recent history of suicide attempt, or suicide risk, was a factor noted in the referral that underpinned the person’s needs for assistance at entry to the episode, as represented by a code.

columns.name: principal_diagnosis
columns.dc:title: Episode - Principal Diagnosis
columns.schema:description: To be defined.

columns.name: other_diagnosis
columns.dc:title: Episode - Other Diagnosis
columns.schema:description: To be defined.

columns.name: medication_antipsychotics
columns.dc:title: Medication - Antipsychotics (N05A)
columns.schema:description: Whether the client is taking prescribed antipsychotics for a mental health condition as assessed at intake assessment, as represented by a code.

columns.name: medication_anxiolytics
columns.dc:title: Medication - Anxiolytics (N05B)
columns.schema:description: Whether the client is taking prescribed anxiolytics for a mental health condition as assessed at intake assessment, as represented by a code.

columns.name: medication_hypnotics
columns.dc:title: Medication - Hypnotics and sedatives (N05C)
columns.schema:description: Whether the client is taking prescribed hypnotics and sedatives for a mental health condition as assessed at intake assessment, as represented by a code.

columns.name: medication_antidepressants
columns.dc:title: Medication - Antidepressants (N06A)
columns.schema:description: Whether the client is taking prescribed antidepressants for a mental health condition as assessed at intake assessment, as represented by a code.

columns.name: medication_psychostimulants
columns.dc:title: Medication - Psychostimulants and nootropics (N06B)
columns.schema:description: Whether the client is taking prescribed psychostimulants and nootropics for a mental health condition as assessed at intake assessment, as represented by a code.

columns.name: referrer_type
columns.dc:title: Episode - Referrer Type
columns.schema:description: To be defined.

columns.name: referrer_entity
columns.dc:title: Episode - Referrer Entity
columns.schema:description: To be defined.

columns.name: organisation_path
columns.dc:title: Organisation Path
columns.schema:description: A sequence of colon separated Organisation Codes that fully specifies the upload organisation.

columns.name: service_contact_key
columns.dc:title: Service Contact Key
columns.schema:description: This is a number or code assigned to each service contact. The Service Contact Key is unique and stable for each service contact at the level of the organisation.

columns.name: service_contact_date
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Date
columns.schema:description: The date of each mental health service contact between a health service provider and patient/client.

columns.name: service_contact_type
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Type
columns.schema:description: The main type of service provided in the service contact, as represented by the service type that accounted for most provider time.

columns.name: service_contact_postcode
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Postcode
columns.schema:description: The Australian postcode where the service contact took place.

columns.name: service_contact_modality
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Modality
columns.schema:description: How the service contact was delivered, as represented by a code.

columns.name: service_contact_venue
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Venue
columns.schema:description: Where the service contact was delivered, as represented by a code.

columns.name: service_contact_duration
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Duration
columns.schema:description: The time from the start to finish of a service contact, as represented by a code.

columns.name: service_contact_copayment
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Copayment
columns.schema:description: The co-payment is the amount paid by the client per session.

columns.name: participation_indicator
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - Client Participation Indicator
columns.schema:description: An indicator of whether the client participated in the service contact, as represented by a code.

columns.name: service_contact_no_show
columns.dc:title: Service Contact - No Show
columns.schema:description: Where an appointment was made for a client, but the client failed to attend the appointment, as represented by a code.

columns.name: organisation_path
columns.dc:title: Organisation Path
columns.schema:description: A sequence of colon separated Organisation Codes that fully specifies the upload organisation.

columns.name: collection_occasion_key
columns.dc:title: Collection Occasion Key
columns.schema:description: This is a number or code assigned to each collection occasion of outcome measures. The Collection Occasion Key is unique and stable for each collection occasion at the level of the organisation.

columns.name: measure
columns.dc:title: Collection Occasion - Measure
columns.schema:description: The name of the measure.

columns.name: measure_date
columns.dc:title: Collection Occasion - Measure Date
columns.schema:description: The date the measure was given.
